    Plot DDM Data

    ddm_traces.Rd

    Plot data.

    Usage

    ddm_traces(
  n_traces = 5,
  time_max = 2,
  step = 0.01,
  drift = 0,
  bs = 1,
  bias = 0.5,
  ndt = 0.2,
  ndt_var = 0.1,
  ...
)

    Arguments

    n_traces

    Number of traces.

    time_max

    Span of the x-axis in seconds.

    step

    Step size in seconds.

    drift

    Drift parameter. Typical range: [-5, 5].

    bs

    boundary separation parameter. Typical range: [0.5, 2].

    bias

    Bias parameter. Default to 0.5*bs.

    ndt

    Non-decision time parameter. Typical range: [0.1, 0.5] s.

    ndt_var

    Variability of non-decision time. Typical range: [0, 0.2] s.

    ...

    Not used for now.

    Examples

    
data_traces <- ddm_traces(n_traces = 5)
